    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-14T05:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-14T05:16:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/902</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-14T12:00:00+01:44">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1914, 12 noon</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 18, 2:35 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Upon receipt last night of reports of Russian victories, a popular demonstration
                    hostile to Austria-Hungary and Germany was suppressed by police and military. It
                    appears likely that Roumania will enter into conflict with Russia within a few
                    days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
